2.Write a JavaScript program to get the current date.
Expected Output :
mm-dd-yyyy, mm/dd/yyyy or dd-mm-yyyy, dd/mm/yyyy

CODE:
function GETDATE(){
    const d = new Date();
    var m=d.getMonth();
    var y=d.getMonth();
    var date=d.getDate();
    const today=`${m} / ${date} / ${y} , ${m} - ${date} - ${y} `; console.log(today);}

console.log(GETDATE());
VM5375:6        6 / 1 / 6      ,           6 - 1 - 6 
